// useDocument
// Provides access to the document list and CRUD operations from the session store.

A thin facade over the session store; no local state. All mutations are delegated to the store.

FUNCTION useDocument() -> UseDocumentReturn                                     EXPORT
  CALLS: useSessionStore (sessionStore)
  Reads documents, selectedDocumentId, and all document actions from the session store using shallow comparison.
  Derives selectedDocument by calling the store's getSelectedDocument getter.
  Exposes: documents, selectedDocumentId, selectedDocument, addDocument, updateDocument, removeDocument,
  selectDocument, setDocuments, getDocumentById, hasDocument.

---

FUNCTION getDocumentById(id) -> Document | undefined
  Finds and returns the document with the given id from the current list, or undefined if not found.

---

FUNCTION hasDocument(id) -> boolean
  Returns true if a document with the given id exists in the current list.
